You can generate a key on Windows with ssh-keygen and import only the public key into EC2.

On Windows: ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "you@example.com" (for Linux instances)

Copy the contents of id_ed25519.pub

In EC2 Key Pairs, choose Import key pair

Paste the public key, name it, and use that key pair when launching instances

Connect with: ssh -i C:\Users\YourUser\.ssh\id_ed25519 ec2-user@<PUBLIC_IP>
